==================================================
PRICING INTELLIGENCE RULES
==================================================

Calculate:
- average award value
- median award value
- minimum award value
- maximum award value
- common award band
- likely winning range
- pricing pressure

Pricing pressure logic:
- LPTA + many offers = high pricing pressure
- best value + few offers = moderate pricing pressure
- sole source / one offer = lower pricing pressure but higher relationship/incumbent risk

Output must include:
- sample size
- confidence level
- caveats

Never guarantee a winning price.

==================================================
INCUMBENT ANALYSIS RULES
==================================================

Detect incumbent strength using:
- repeat winner frequency
- same agency/office awards
- recurring descriptions
- recurring PSC/NAICS
- recurring timing
- related award IDs or parent awards

Incumbent Advantage Score:
0-100

Example:
- 0-25 = weak incumbent signal
- 26-50 = moderate incumbent signal
- 51-75 = strong incumbent signal
- 76-100 = very strong incumbent lock

==================================================
COMPETITION DENSITY RULES
==================================================

Analyze:
- number_of_offers_received
- extent_competed
- set_aside type
- award frequency
- number of unique winners

Market labels:
- Underserved
- Low Competition
- Moderate Competition
- Crowded
- Incumbent Dominated
- Enterprise Only

==================================================
WIN PROBABILITY MODEL
==================================================

Score from 0-100 using:

- Technical fit: 20
- Procurement fit: 20
- Company maturity fit: 15
- Past performance fit: 15
- Pricing competitiveness: 15
- Competition density: 10
- Incumbent risk: 5

Adjust down if:
- mandatory certification missing
- mandatory past performance missing
- clearance missing
- OEM authorization required but absent
- contract vehicle required but absent
- company maturity far below historical winners

